<sect1>
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <para>
The Microsoft Installer packages are available in a number of localized translations.
 To specify a specific localization or language use the TRANSFORMS property when invoking
 msiexec to install.
  </para>
  <para>
<ulink url="https://translation.torproject.org/projects/vidaliainstaller/">See the Tor Project Translation site for additional information</ulink>.
  </para>


  <sect2 id="langs">
   <title>Supported Package Languages</title>
   <para><literallayout>
en, cs, de, es, fa, fi, fr, he, it, nl, pl, pt, ro, ru, sv
   </literallayout></para>
   <para>
Ex. torvm-de.msi
   </para>
   <para><literallayout>
   </literallayout></para>
  </sect2>


  <sect2 id="transxlate">
   <title>Supported Translation Transforms</title>
   <para><literallayout>
TRANSFORMS=:en (default codepage)
TRANSFORMS=:cs
TRANSFORMS=:de
TRANSFORMS=:es
TRANSFORMS=:fa
TRANSFORMS=:fi
TRANSFORMS=:fr
TRANSFORMS=:he
TRANSFORMS=:it
TRANSFORMS=:nl
TRANSFORMS=:pl
TRANSFORMS=:pt
TRANSFORMS=:ro
TRANSFORMS=:ru
TRANSFORMS=:sv
   </literallayout></para>
  </sect2>
</sect1>


